      • optimalTreeGenerator

        public java.util.List<java.lang.String> optimalTreeGenerator(java.lang.String alignmentName,
                                                    java.util.List<java.lang.String> trees,
                                                    BinaryTree<java.lang.String> originalTree,
                                                    java.lang.String[] OUT)
        Generates the best tree(s) from all the trees and their HYPHY script results. The tree with the lowest AIC value is considered the best root. The consequent nodes have likelihood values generated from their tree's HYPHY SchmodelTest.bf script results. (i.e. the tree with the node sequence as the root has it's value result assigned to the node).
        Parameters:
        alignmentName - the name of the alignment (used to output results under correct name)
        trees - all the trees in String format
        originalTree - the orginal BinaryTree that the roots were based off of
        OUT - the results produced by SchmodelTest.bf HYPHY script
        Returns:
        a List of the best tree(s)

      • assignLike

        public void assignLike(BinaryTree<java.lang.String> tree,
              BinaryTree<java.lang.String> node,
              java.util.List<java.lang.String> trees,
              double[] values)
        Likelihood values are assigned to the tree. The original tree is used and then a copy rerooted on the node to compare to the list of trees already rerooted. Original tree used as rerooting will be same as before. Rerooting a different tree may produce same topology, but different absolute orientation, so harder to find equal. The value for the tree is then set as the node's value. Because node is pointer, no return value required.
        Parameters:
        tree - the original tree that was used to produce reroot
        node - the node to be assigned a value
        trees - all the trees that have already been rerooted
        values - array of values corresponding to trees index

      • run

        public final void run()
        Running method. Alignment files in Input are used to generate a corresponding tree file using FastTree. The alignment to be processed is selected from a combobox. The alignment then has it's tree rerooted in all possible ways (with same topology). The rerooted trees are assigned likelihood values using a HYPHY script. These likelihood values are used to populate the best tree. The tree(s) is output to Output under an appropriately named folder. Files relating to alignment under Input are deleted.
